:Sb"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/setPhysicsProcess(enable:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Enables or disables physics (i.e. fixed framerate) processing. When a node is being processed, it will receive a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/notificationPhysicsProcess","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" at a fixed (usually 60 FPS, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Engine\/physicsTicksPerSecond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to change) interval (and the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/_physicsProcess(delta:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" callback will be called if exists). Enabled automatically if ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/_physicsProcess(delta:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" is overridden. Any calls to this before ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/_ready()"},{"text":" will be ignored.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol"}}}